# Healthcare Backend API Test File
# Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### API Documentation
GET http://localhost:3000/api

### Register User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. John Smith",
  "email": "john.smith@hospital.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}

### Login User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.smith@hospital.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}

### Create Patient (Replace TOKEN with actual JWT token from login)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@email.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "date_of_birth": "1985-03-20",
  "gender": "female",
  "address": "456 Oak Avenue, Springfield, IL 62701",
  "medical_history": "Hypertension, no known drug allergies"
}

### Get All Patients
GET http://localhost:3000/api/patients
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### Get Specific Patient
GET http://localhost:3000/api/patients/1
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### Update Patient
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/patients/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

{
  "name": "Jane Doe Updated",
  "email": "jane.doe.updated@email.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "date_of_birth": "1985-03-20",
  "gender": "female",
  "address": "789 Pine Street, Springfield, IL 62701",
  "medical_history": "Hypertension, diabetes type 2, no known drug allergies"
}

